<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="average-adj">average <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'ævərɪdʒ/    美 /'ævərɪdʒ/  </p>
<p>[无比较级]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 平均的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Scientists believe the world’s average temperature has risen by about 0.8℃ since 1900.  
科学家认为自1900年以来，世界平均温度已经升高了约0.8℃。</p><footer>2012 四川</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The average number of electronic devices rose from four per household in 1992 to 13 in 2007.
平均每户家庭的电子设备数量从1992年的4件上升到了2007年的13件。</p><footer>2018 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>中等的；适中的</strong></h4>
<p>normal or typical：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>children <strong>of average intelligence</strong> 
智力一般的儿童</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He was in his late twenties and <strong>of average height</strong>.
他年近三十，中等个头。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>平常的；普遍的</strong></h4>
<p>not special; ordinary：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Freddy was an average student, but not an average person.
弗雷迪是一名普通的学生，但却不是一个普通的人。</p><footer>2017 全国</footer></div></div>